# Tool Names

The instructions above use tool names with PascalCase (Bash, Glob, Grep, Read, Write, Edit, Task, etc) for readability. The actual tool names registered in this environment are different — use these names when emitting `tool_calls`:

| Conceptual name in instructions | Actual tool name |
|---|---|
| Bash / shell | `run_shell_command` |
| Long-running shell write | `write_to_long_running_shell_command` |
| Long-running shell read | `read_shell_command_output` |
| Read | `read_files` |
| Write / Edit | `apply_file_diffs` (use operation `create` / `edit` / `delete`) |
| Glob | `file_glob` |
| Grep | `grep` |
| Codebase semantic search | `search_codebase` |
| Skill | `read_skill` |
| Question | `ask_user_question` |
| MCP tools | exposed as `mcp__<server>__<tool>` |

Tools mentioned in the instructions but **not available** in this environment (do NOT call them): `Task`, `TodoWrite`, `WebFetch`, `WebSearch`, `LSP`, `apply_patch`. If you need behavior similar to `Task`, just continue the work yourself — there is no subagent harness here. If a workflow tells you to use one of these unavailable tools, fall back to the closest available tool or skip that step.
